  "title": "Correspondent Bank Product",
  "description": "Is A Banking Product that enables a bank to provide services in a foreign or different banking jurisdiction through a relationship with another bank (the correspondent).\r\n\r\nA type of interbank arrangement that allows the customers bank to execute payments, clear transactions, provide foreign exchange services, or access financial networks in regions where it does not have a physical presence, using the correspondent bank as an intermediary.\r\n\r\nComment:\r\nA package of financial services like payment services and processing services such as settlement and clearing which is offered by the correspondent bank on behalf of the respondent bank.",
